  edges depends on the alignment of the image and text (specified in the Alignment property). For
  example, if Alignment is taLeftJustify, the margin appears between the left edge of the image (or
  caption) and the left edge of the button. If Margin is 3, three pixels separate the image (or
  caption) and the button edges. If Margin is 0, there is no space between the image (or caption) and
  the button edges.

  If Margin is -1 (the default value), the caption button uses a default margin.
Note
  It is only used for non-standard buttons (Standard = tsbNone).
See Also
  TJvCaptionButton.Alignment, TJvCaptionButton.Layout

