@@TJvCaptionButton.ParentShowHint
Summary
  Determines where a control looks to find out if its Help \Hint should be shown.
Description
  Use ParentShowHint to ensure that all the controls on a form either uniformly show their Help Hints
  or uniformly do not show them.

  If ParentShowHint is true, the control uses the \ShowHint property value of its parent. If
  ParentShowHint is false, the control uses the value of its own ShowHint property.

  To provide Help Hints for only selected controls on a form, set the \ShowHint property for those
  controls that should have Help Hints to true, and ParentShowHint becomes false automatically.
Note
  Enable or disable all Help Hints for the entire application using the \ShowHint property of the
  application object.
See Also
  TJvCaptionButton.Hint, TJvCaptionButton.ParentForm, TJvCaptionButton.ShowHint

